Consider the following series of arithmetic expressions.
a = 18;
b = 6;
c = 7;

a /=  b;
b -= 4;
c = a + b - c;

Which of the following statements is true?
a == 3 and b == 2 and c == 17
a == 4 and b == 2 and c == 17
a == 3 and b == 2 and c == -2

Consider the following series of arithmetic expressions.
a = 11;
b = 18;
c = 4;

a++;
b -= a + c / 2;
c = 5 * c % 5;

Which of the following statements is true?
a == 12 and b == 4 and c == 0
a == 12 and b == 8 and c == 0
a == 12 and b == 8 and c == 9

Consider the following series of arithmetic expressions.
a = 7;
b = 11;
c = 3;

a = a + 25 % b;
b = 2 – c * 2;
c = c * 4 % a;

Which of the following statements is true?
a == 15 and b == 1 and c == 2
a == 10 and b == -4 and c == 2
a == 15 and b == -2 and c == 5

Consider the following:
int a = 7;

int b = 4;

int c = -2;



a = b + 3 * c;

b -= 5 + c;

c = b – 4 / a;
System.out.println(a + " " + b + " " + c);


What will be the output of this program?
-20 1 4.2
-2 1 3
-2 3 5

